  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"i\" in iPhone?",
  "response": "The \"i\" in iPhone originally stood for \"internet\" when Apple first introduced the iMac in 1998. Steve Jobs explained that the \"i\" symbolized several things:\n\n1. Internet\n2. Individual\n3. Innovative\n4. Instructive\n5. Informative\n\nOver time, the \"i\" prefix became a signature branding element for Apple products like iPod, iPad, iTunes, and iPhone. While it initially referenced internet connectivity, it has since become more of a recognizable brand identifier for Apple products.",
